               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Douce_389-item1" n="1" class="#topographica">
                     <title type="desc" key="work_13130">Map of <placeName key="place_7004540">Palestine</placeName></title>
                     <note>East is at the top. A version of the ‘large Burchard map’ (P. D. A. Harvey, <title>Medieval maps of the Holy Land</title> (2012), 94-106), with inscriptions deriving from <persName role="aut" key="person_100899506">Burchard of Mount Sion</persName>, <title key="work_1176">Descriptio terrae sanctae</title>. A table of distances at the north (left) side of the map derives partly from <persName role="aut" key="person_12386025">Rorgo Fretellus</persName>, <title key="work_6183">Liber locorum sanctorum terrae Ierusalem</title>, partly from an unknown source or sources; English translation of this list in P. Arad, ‘Pilgrimage, cartography, and devotion: William Wey's map of the Holy Land’, <title>Viator</title> 43 (2012), 318-19.</note>
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="roll">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support><material>parchment</material>. <objectType>Original format uncertain, but damage on the lower edge shows it was kept as a roll at some point, and it was described as a 'rotulus' in the 1840 Douce catalogue (Harvey, p. 135).</objectType></support>
                        <extent>3 membranes
                           <dimensions unit="mm" type="overall">
                              <height>413</height>
                              <width>c. 2149</width>
                           </dimensions></extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>One scribe (Harvey, p. 137).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Coloured map. (P&amp;A iii. 751)</decoNote>
                     <decoNote>Each membrane by a different draughtsman (Harvey, pp. 137, 139-40).</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
