                     <origPlace>
                        <country key="place_7002445">English</country>
                     </origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Sometimes identified with the ‘mappa of the holy lond’ owned by the 15th-century pilgrim <persName role="fmo" cert="low" key="person_2648516">William Wey</persName>, but it corresponds only in part to the map described by Wey (Harvey, pp. 138-9; cf. Arad, 309-14 for the contraary argument).</provenance>
